.TH "pci_sriov_configure_simple" 9 "pci_sriov_configure_simple" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_sriov_configure_simple \- helper to configure SR-IOV
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pci_sriov_configure_simple
.BI "(struct pci_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "int nr_virtfn "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the PCI device
.IP "nr_virtfn" 12
number of virtual functions to enable, 0 to disable
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Enable or disable SR-IOV for devices that don't require any PF setup
before enabling SR-IOV.  Return value is negative on error, or number of
VFs allocated on success.
